{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:philemon.1",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "philemon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Philemon 1 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy, a brother: to Philemon, our beloved and fellow labourer,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:2",
      "text": "And to Appia, our dearest sister, and to Archippus, our fellow soldier, and to the church which is in thy house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you and peace, from God our Father and from the Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:4",
      "text": "I give thanks to my God, always making a remembrance of thee in my prayers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:5",
      "text": "Hearing of thy charity and faith, which thou hast in the Lord Jesus and towards all the saints:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:6",
      "text": "That the communication of thy faith may be made evident in the acknowledgment of every good work that is in you in Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:7",
      "text": "For I have had great joy and consolation in thy charity, because the bowels of the saints have been refreshed by thee, brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:8",
      "text": "Wherefore, though I have much confidence in Christ Jesus to command thee that which is to the purpose:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:9",
      "text": "For charity sake I rather beseech, whereas thou art such a one, as Paul, an old man and now a prisoner also of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:10",
      "text": "I beseech thee for my son, whom I have begotten in my bands, Onesimus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:11",
      "text": "Who hath been heretofore unprofitable to thee but now is profitable both to me and thee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:12",
      "text": "Whom I have sent back to thee. And do thou receive him as my own bowels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:13",
      "text": "Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he might have ministered to me in the bands of the gospel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:14",
      "text": "But without thy counsel I would do nothing: that thy good deed might not be as it were of necessity, but voluntary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:15",
      "text": "For perhaps he therefore departed for a season from thee that thou mightest receive him again for ever:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:16",
      "text": "Not now as a servant, but instead of a servant, a most dear brother, especially to me. But how much more to thee, both in the flesh and in the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:17",
      "text": "If therefore thou count me a partner, receive him as myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:18",
      "text": "And if he hath wronged thee in any thing or is in thy debt, put that to my account.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:19",
      "text": "I Paul have written it with my own hand: I will repay it: not to say to thee that thou owest me thy own self also.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:20",
      "text": "Yea, brother. May I enjoy thee in the Lord! Refresh my bowels in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:21",
      "text": "Trusting in thy obedience, I have written to thee: knowing that thou wilt also do more than I say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:22",
      "text": "But withal prepare me also a lodging. For I hope that through your prayers I shall be given unto you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:23",
      "text": "There salute thee Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:24",
      "text": "Mark, Aristarchus, Demas and Luke, my fellow labourers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:philemon.1.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:25",
      "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
